    <p>The catchphrase “There’s an app for that” continues to ring true as more and more businesses, large and small, go&nbsp;mobile. A mobile app is a software application made for handheld devices, namely smartphones. As mobile device usage continues to grow, apps allow for companies to connect to their customers more directly than ever before. They bring a slew of capabilities into a business’ toolbox that websites alone don’t offer. Let’s dive into one of these most important features: <strong>Push Notifications</strong>.</p>
    <p><em>First, what is a <strong>push notification</strong>? Through a mobile app, a push notification will alert&nbsp;a user to events, news, or&nbsp;product offerings. Even when an app is closed, these messages will appear to a device’s user. In short, push notifications bring&nbsp;your customers the most up-to-date information when they’re on the go.</em></p>
    <h3><strong>Push Notification Benefits</strong></h3>
